README for zaproxy-weekly-bin

NOTES

    How-to fix Java Look-and-Feel
    -----------------------------

    Add the following lines into ~/.bash_profile:

    xprop -root -f _NET_WM_NAME 32a -set _NET_WM_NAME LG3D
    export _JAVA_AWT_WM_NONREPARENTING=1

    And, in case if you have terminus-like fonts systemwide,
    add this line (disabled antialiasing mode):

    export _JAVA_OPTIONS="-Dawt.useSystemAAFontSettings=off -Dswing.aatext=false -Dswing.defaultlaf=com.sun.java.swing.plaf.gtk.GTKLookAndFeel -Dswing.crossplatformlaf=com.sun.java.swing.plaf.gtk.GTKLookAndFeel"

    Otherwise, add this (enabled antialiasing mode):

    export _JAVA_OPTIONS="-Dawt.useSystemAAFontSettings=on -Dswing.aatext=true -Dswing.defaultlaf=com.sun.java.swing.plaf.gtk.GTKLookAndFeel -Dswing.crossplatformlaf=com.sun.java.swing.plaf.gtk.GTKLookAndFeel"
